# Lessons Learned

## Documentation is Rare in Small Businesses
Many small venues operate with little or no infrastructure documentation.

Creating a device inventory and network diagram significantly improves supportability.

## Default Credentials Are Still Common
Several devices were still using factory default credentials. This remains one of the most common vulnerabilities in small networks.

## Security Improvements Must Not Interrupt Operations
Remediation work was performed during off-peak hours to avoid disrupting business systems such as POS and security cameras.

## Incremental Security Improvements Are Effective
Even small changes such as firmware updates, credential rotation, and secure remote access significantly reduced overall risk.
